==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: obliterated
<hw>obliterated</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>destroyed so
thoroughly as to be unrecognizable or imperceptible.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> wiped out, obliterate.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>made illegible or imperceptible by erasing or
abrading away; -- of writing or surface designs on objects.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> blotted out, obliterated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>obliterating</ent>⟦br⟧
